  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Sear the beef until browned, then set aside.",
    "Sauté the onion, carrot, and celery until tender.",
    "Add the lemongrass, beef broth, red wine, tomato paste, thyme, salt, and pepper.",
    "Return the beef to the pot and bring to a boil.",
    "Cover and transfer to the oven, where it will braise for 2 1/2 hours.",
    "Remove the pot from the oven and stir in the brown sugar.",
    "Simmer the stew over low heat for an additional 30 minutes.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped fresh herbs.",
    "Strain the stew before serving, discarding the solids.",
    "Skim off any excess fat that rises to the surface.",
    "Serve with crusty bread or over egg noodles."
